and Paul Bunyany,

411
00:15:20.044 --> 00:15:23.756  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
and I’m like some sissy man
with pinkish cheeks
and a turned-out heel.

412
00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:26.050  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
It’s a caricature.

413
00:15:26.134 --> 00:15:28.427  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
What matters
is what it represents.

414
00:15:28.511 --> 00:15:33.057  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
My daddy making this for us
means he’s accepted us
for who we are.

415
00:15:33.141 --> 00:15:34.600  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Don’t you get that?

416
00:15:34.684 --> 00:15:38.813  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:70.50% 
I never really thought
about it that way.

417
00:15:34.684 --> 00:15:38.813  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.66% 
No. You hadn’t.

418
00:15:41.149 --> 00:15:46.195  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I’m just being sensitive.
I need to have a thicker skin.
I’m really, really sorry.

419
00:15:47.321 --> 00:15:50.407  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
No, don’t– Don’t–
Don’t be sorry. No.

420
00:15:50.491 --> 00:15:53.452  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
And I don’t want something
at the wedding
that makes you uncomfortable.

421
00:15:53.536 --> 00:15:56.455  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
No, that doesn’t seem fair.
I’ve used up all my vetoes.

422
00:15:58.207 --> 00:16:01.335  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Well, if it–
I guess if it makes
you feel better,

423
00:16:01.419 --> 00:16:05.047  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I could give you one more veto
if you give me one more too.

424
00:16:06.007 --> 00:16:07.424  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Okay, sure.

425
00:16:07.508 --> 00:16:09.009  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
And in the future,
if there’s anything–

426
00:16:09.093 --> 00:16:11.220  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
The wedding singer.

427
00:16:16.726 --> 00:16:19.395  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
Okay. Thanks, Daddy.
I’ll send you the perfect
picture to model it on.

428
00:16:20.229 --> 00:16:21.688  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Phone Beeps ]

429
00:16:21.772 --> 00:16:23.566  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Chuckling ]

430
00:16:25.359 --> 00:16:28.737  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
After today,
I’m convinced our landfills
are 10% hair.

431
00:16:28.821 --> 00:16:32.366  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>Ay,</i> yes.
I forgot how exhausting this is.

432
00:16:32.450 --> 00:16:34.785  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
Well, all we have to do
is meet the clients
back at the apartment.

433
00:16:34.869 --> 00:16:38.872  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
- Then we can head home.
- <i>Ay,</i> no. I’m too tired now.
Let’s reschedule.

434
00:16:38.956 --> 00:16:42.584  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
- Really? Again?
- Yes. Let’s meet them
next week.

435
00:16:42.668 --> 00:16:44.837  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
And besides,
we’re late for Jay’s party.

436
00:16:44.921 --> 00:16:48.090  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Well, I’m not letting you
go home looking like this.

437
00:16:48.174 --> 00:16:49.508  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
You’re a little ratty
back here.

438
00:16:49.592 --> 00:16:50.968  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Gasps ]
<i>Ay,</i> no.

439
00:16:51.052 --> 00:16:54.263  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
No, no, no.
I got it.
Yep. You just relax.

440
00:16:55.473 --> 00:16:58.517  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Oh, what a day, huh?

441
00:16:58.601 --> 00:17:01.186  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Being back here must bring up
a lot of memories.

442
00:17:01.270 --> 00:17:04.022  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:69.06% 
Oh, yeah.

443
00:17:01.270 --> 00:17:04.022  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.23% 
Maybe even
some emotions.

444
00:17:04.106 --> 00:17:05.524  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Yeah. It feels weird.

445
00:17:05.608 --> 00:17:08.360  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
"Weird" is an adjective,
not an emotion, but go on.

446
00:17:08.444 --> 00:17:12.030  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, it’s just that my life now
is so different than before.

447
00:17:12.114 --> 00:17:13.448  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:89.67% 
So much easier.

448
00:17:13.532 --> 00:17:15.200  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
And that
makes you feel–

449
00:17:15.284 --> 00:17:17.286  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:75.93% 
Good.

450
00:17:15.284 --> 00:17:17.286  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
And also–

451
00:17:17.370 --> 00:17:19.538  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:75.93% 
And bad.

452
00:17:17.370 --> 00:17:19.538  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Why?

453
00:17:19.622 --> 00:17:22.541  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
I don’t know.

454
00:17:19.622 --> 00:17:22.541  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.66% 
Come on now, Gloria.

455
00:17:22.625 --> 00:17:26.628  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I don’t know.
I guess it just makes me feel
a little ashamed.

456
00:17:26.712 --> 00:17:31.049  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Now what in the world
do you have to be ashamed of?

457
00:17:31.133 --> 00:17:33.927  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
It’s just that, you know,
before when I used to live here,

458
00:17:34.011 --> 00:17:36.555  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
I used to work for every penny.

459
00:17:36.639 --> 00:17:38.974  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
I would stand
on my own two feet.

460
00:17:39.058 --> 00:17:41.226  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
Now I just stand
on expensive shoes...

461
00:17:41.310 --> 00:17:43.061  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
that Jay buys for me.

462
00:17:43.145 --> 00:17:45.397  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Is that why it’s so hard
to let go of the apartment?

463
00:17:45.481 --> 00:17:46.982  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
No, Phil,
it’s not that–

464
00:17:47.066 --> 00:17:49.693  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:75.93% 
Gloria.

465
00:17:47.066 --> 00:17:49.693  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
Maybe.

466
00:17:49.777 --> 00:17:51.445  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:89.67% 
Gloria.

467
00:17:51.529 --> 00:17:54.156  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Yes. It’s the last piece
of the old me.

468
00:17:54.240 --> 00:17:55.365  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:89.67% 
Mmm.

469
00:17:55.449 --> 00:17:57.284  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>¡Ay, no!</i> Enough!
You’re going too deep.

470
00:17:57.368 --> 00:17:58.660  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
I’m sorry. I’m sorry.

471
00:17:58.744 --> 00:18:00.662  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
But I think you’re
looking at this all wrong.

472
00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:02.247  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
The old you
hasn’t gone anywhere.

473
00:18:02.331 --> 00:18:04.499  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I see it in the way
you’re raising Manny and Joe.

474
00:18:04.583 --> 00:18:06.710  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
The way you care for Jay.

475
00:18:06.794 --> 00:18:09.505  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
You never take anyone
or anything for granted.

476
00:18:11.215 --> 00:18:14.593  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
You worked hard for years
without knowing that things
were gonna get better.

477
00:18:14.677 --> 00:18:16.428  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
And then the universe
rewarded you.

478
00:18:16.512 --> 00:18:18.764  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
There’s nothing
to be ashamed of.

479
00:18:18.848 --> 00:18:21.683  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
So you’re not mad at me
because I don’t want to
sell the apartment?

480
00:18:21.767 --> 00:18:25.103  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
No. You’ll know
when you’re ready,
and I’ll be here.

481
00:18:25.187 --> 00:18:27.397  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>Ay,</i> Phil.

482
00:18:27.481 --> 00:18:30.692  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:69.06% 
You’re the best.

483
00:18:27.481 --> 00:18:30.692  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:84.23% 
Oh.
[ Laughs ]

484
00:18:30.776 --> 00:18:32.862  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
There’s no one like you.

485
00:18:38.075 --> 00:18:39.826  position:80.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Sniffs ]
Mmm!

486
00:18:39.910 --> 00:18:41.453  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:84.33% 
Mm-mmm.
Yuck!

487
00:18:41.537 --> 00:18:45.207  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Claire, that looks so good.
I can’t wait to try it.

488
00:18:45.291 --> 00:18:47.376  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Thank you.
Oh.

489
00:18:50.463 --> 00:18:52.381  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Something
has happened here.

490
00:18:54.216 --> 00:18:57.135  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
Well, you’ll all be happy
to know that our search
for the cake topper...

491
00:18:57.219 --> 00:18:59.137  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
unearthed a number
of family treasures.

492
00:18:59.221 --> 00:19:01.139  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Come on, Cam.
We’re eating over here.

493
00:19:01.223 --> 00:19:03.892  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Wait. Didn’t I give you this
for Father’s Day?

494
00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:06.353  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
- And that?
- You see how this dog is.

495
00:19:06.437 --> 00:19:08.855  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Gasps ]
My karaoke microphone.

496
00:19:08.939 --> 00:19:11.817  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Jay, check it out.
The other walkie-talkie!

497
00:19:11.901 --> 00:19:15.946  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Shame on you, Jay Pritchett.
You have used this dog to bury
the things that you hate.

498
00:19:16.030 --> 00:19:18.490  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
- [ Alex ] Yeah.
- Since when do you need help
burying things?

499
00:19:18.574 --> 00:19:21.326  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
Calm down. She buries
stuff of mine too. Look.

500
00:19:21.410 --> 00:19:24.079  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Everybody at the office
bought me this clock last month.

501
00:19:24.163 --> 00:19:25.872  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Honey, what’s the matter
with you?

502
00:19:25.956 --> 00:19:28.208  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:70.50% 
That’s a question
that maybe you should answer.

503
00:19:25.956 --> 00:19:28.208  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.66% 
Oh, my gosh–

504
00:19:28.292 --> 00:19:30.836  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
[ All Talking At Once ]

505
00:19:30.920 --> 00:19:33.338  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
<i>[ Claire ]</i>
<i>"Here’s to 40 years</i>
<i>in the business.</i>

506
00:19:33.422 --> 00:19:36.092  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>Enjoy your new timer,</i>
<i>old-timer."</i>

507
00:19:37.593 --> 00:19:39.553  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
Suddenly, it made sense.

508
00:19:39.637 --> 00:19:43.223  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
In my dad’s mind,
I was reaching for a torch
he wasn’t ready to pass.

509
00:19:43.307 --> 00:19:46.935  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
Sure. Someday I’m gonna
take over his business,
but not tonight.

510
00:19:47.019 --> 00:19:49.604  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>Tonight is still Jay’s night.</i>

511
00:19:49.688 --> 00:19:51.357  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Pot Clatters ]

512
00:19:54.610 --> 00:19:56.445  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
So, Dad–

513
00:19:57.863 --> 00:20:00.574  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Turns out I did have
a bunch of questions
for you last week,

514
00:20:00.658 --> 00:20:02.409  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
but I didn’t want
to bother you with them.

515
00:20:02.493 --> 00:20:04.202  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I didn’t want you to think
I couldn’t handle it.

516
00:20:04.286 --> 00:20:06.955  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
There’s no shame
in asking for help.
You can always call.

517
00:20:07.039 --> 00:20:10.626  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Well, I won’t need to.
You’ll be in the office
down the hall, right?

518
00:20:12.128 --> 00:20:13.295  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Right.

519
00:20:15.297 --> 00:20:17.716  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
<i>[ Phil On Walkie-talkie ]</i>
<i>Goldilocks to Papa Bear.</i>
<i>Goldilocks to Papa Bear.</i>

520
00:20:17.800 --> 00:20:19.510  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>Come in, Papa Bear.</i>

521
00:20:24.306 --> 00:20:25.808  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:89.67% 
This is Papa Bear.

522
00:20:26.976 --> 00:20:29.061  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>On location</i>
<i>in the garage, Papa Bear.</i>

523
00:20:29.145 --> 00:20:31.439  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
<i>Got some cocoa</i>
<i>with your name on it.</i>
<i>What’s your 20?</i>

524
00:20:36.735 --> 00:20:38.403  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:5.00% 
Oh, what the hell?

525
00:20:38.487 --> 00:20:40.739  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:5.00% 
- What’s going on?
- The kids unfriended me again.

526
00:20:40.823 --> 00:20:43.825  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
How am I supposed to know
what’s going on in their lives
if they never talk to me?

527
00:20:43.909 --> 00:20:46.745  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:5.00% 
Honey, I got this.

528
00:20:46.829 --> 00:20:49.289  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
Yeah, it’s been kind of
a rough year.

529
00:20:49.373 --> 00:20:52.000  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:5.00% 
Mm-hmm.

530
00:20:49.373 --> 00:20:52.000  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:18.74% 
New school,
new kids,

531
00:20:52.084 --> 00:20:53.502  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
and I’m taking advice
about girls...

532
00:20:53.586 --> 00:20:55.295  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
from a kid who has
his own shoe buffer.

533
00:20:55.379 --> 00:20:56.171  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:5.00% 
What?

534
00:20:56.255 --> 00:20:57.964  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
I tried beer.

535
00:20:58.048 --> 00:21:00.467  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:5.00% 
Oh.

536
00:21:00.551 --> 00:21:02.511  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
Wow, Dad, this feels great.

537
00:21:02.595 --> 00:21:03.929  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:5.00% 
Good. Good.

538
00:21:04.013 --> 00:21:06.139  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
Y-You’re sure there’s–
there’s nothing on your mind?

539
00:21:06.223 --> 00:21:10.352  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Sighs ]
No. Why do you ask, Dad?
You seem upset about something.

540
00:21:10.436 --> 00:21:11.937  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
It’s just you reach
a certain age,

541
00:21:12.021 --> 00:21:14.439  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
and you start to wonder,
"Am I everything
I wanted to be?"

542
00:21:14.523 --> 00:21:16.691  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I mean, am I selling houses,
or am I just selling out?

543
00:21:16.775 --> 00:21:18.985  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
Anything else?

544
00:21:16.775 --> 00:21:18.985  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.66% 
